# Program Settings Dialog (Mandatory — Do Not Regress)

**Status:** Verified working on Windows (2026-07). **프로그램 설정** (`ProgramSettingsDialog`) uses category **QGroupBox** sections and **tooltips** for all option detail — not inline `HintLabel` paragraphs under each row.

## Required layout

| Group | Options |
| ----- | ------- |
| **기능 실행** | Auto-select running feature, focus target on profile switch, run without target window, log max lines |
| **시작·종료** | Launch at Windows startup, close to tray |
| **업데이트** | Periodic update check + interval spin, auto-install updates |
| **권한·호환** | Run as administrator (+ elevated status line when applicable) |
| **템플릿 매칭** | ImageFind capture mode combo |
| **화면 표시** | Default click/run feedback, window-pick animation (summary + **설정…**) |

Top intro: one short `QLabel` (muted via `secondaryHintTextColor`) — tells users to hover for tooltips and notes profile vs global scope.

## Adding a new option (mandatory)

1. Place the control in the **correct existing group** (add a new `QGroupBox` only when no group fits).
2. **Label:** short, beginner-friendly Korean — no multi-line explanation in the label.
3. **Detail:** `widget->setToolTip(...)` on the checkbox, label, combo, or spin — never a sibling `HintLabel` under the row.
4. **Group overview:** optional one-line tooltip on the `QGroupBox` title.
5. **Persistence:** `ProgramSettings` + `QSettings` key; document in AGENTS.md §5.7 / §11 when user-facing.

## Anti-patterns

- Inline `HintLabel` (or multi-line grey text) under every checkbox in program settings
- Flat ungrouped list of all options
- Long option labels that duplicate tooltip text
- `changeEvent` → `setStyleSheet` on settings widgets

